Inner Chapters (内篇):
1. 逍遙遊 (Xiaoyao You / Carefree Wandering) — Kun the giant fish transforms into the Peng bird; the mushroom of a morning; the cicada laughing at the great bird; Liezi riding the wind
2. 齊物論 (Qi Wu Lun / On the Equalization of Things) — the pipes of Heaven; Zhuangzi dreams of being a butterfly; the sage does not take sides; the hinge of the Dao
3. 養生主 (Yangsheng Zhu / Nourishing the Lord of Life) — Cook Ding and the ox; following natural structure; Prince Hui's cook
4. 人間世 (Renjian Shi / In the World of Men) — the useless tree; Confucius advises Yan Hui; the carpenter's dream
5. 大宗師 (Da Zong Shi / The Great Teacher) — accepting death as transformation; Lady Yu and her companions; sitting and forgetting (zuowang)
6. 應帝王 (Ying Diwang / Fitting for Emperors and Kings) — Hundun (chaos) dies when given seven orifices; the sage ruler governs by non-action

